<br>
The trick is getting the correct pause in between the spells- this pause is made up of the cast time of the spell plus the time it takes to recover from it- the cast time is easy- each spell tells u it- the recovery time is more trial and error rather than an exact science.   For example as a chanter you may want to cast Tashani (lowers mobs MR) followed by slow onto a mob- now Tashani's cast time is 1.0<br>
so the pause time woulf be 10 plus estimated recovery time- by trial and error( and very patient tuition from an old friend of mine) I found the following lines and pause work in my setup- where Tashani is in spell slot #2 and slow in spell slot #7<br>
<br>
Line one---- /cast 2<br>
Line two---- /pause 30  &lt;----- ( cast time plus recovery)<br>
Line three-- /cast 7<br>
Line four--  %T Slowed for your hacking pleasure! <br>
<br>
(%T = mob targeted for thos who dont know)<br>
<br>
So, how usefull any of you will find this i dont know, but it made my day<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br>
<br>
Happy hacking!!<br>
