<br>
Furthermore, you can also use the /pause command on the same line as another social by separating the commands with a comma. Even though the pause command is specified first, it is executed AFTER the command on the same line.<br>
<br>
For example:<br>
<br>
/sit off<br>
/pause 100,/cast 1<br>
/sit on<br>
<br>
It is important to note that the comma can only be used to separate a /pause command from another, and MUST be specified first on the line.<br>
<br>
Thus the pause command enables a caster to have even more spells weaved into one hot key <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  For example I could do this though it would aggro me like hell:<br>
<br>
/sit off<br>
/pause 40,/cast 8<br>
/pause 80,/cast 6<br>
/pause 60,/cast 5<br>
/g %T is snared and double DoTed...and on me!<br>
<br>
